<h1>the Scripture</h1>


<p>Peace be with you!</p>

<p>We are working to create special software which will help us, God willing,
to study the scripture together, write commentaries and make new translations.</p>

<p>You can study the
<A href="/x/quiki/bible/index.html">Bible</A>
and
<A href="/x/quiki/quran/index.html">Quran</A>
with our new scripture viewer, quiki.&nbsp; Quiki is now "download friendly", 
you can download pages for using offline.</p>

<p>Here is the machine-readable, plain-text <A href="bible">Bible</A> and <A
href="quran">Quran</A>.&nbsp; Every chapter or surah has its own file, and each
verse is a single line.&nbsp; There are many texts and translations.</p>

<p>We have prepared a new "no frills" latin transliteration of the Quran, <A
href="/quran/tlt/">quran/tlt</A>.&nbsp; It maps Arabic letters to Latin
characters, and does not include additional vowels or punctuation.&nbsp; We
hope you find it easy to read.&nbsp; You can use <A
href="/x/quiki/quran/index.html">quiki</A> to view it.&nbsp; Here is <A
href="quran_tlt.html">more about quran/tlt</A>.</p>

<p>We are collecting a list of links to resources.&nbsp; Please contact us by
sending email to <a href="mailto:word@nipl.net">word@nipl.net</a> if you can
tell us about other resources, or to find out more about this project.</p>

<!--p>You can download a <A href="word.zip">70 Mb zip</A> of the texts.</p-->

<p>Please join <A href="http://nipl.net/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo/word">our email list</A>,
God willing we can share our understanding of the word and God.</p>

<p>There is a good list for discussion of the Quran - OQS: <A
href="http://www.topica.com/lists/OQS/read">http://www.topica.com/lists/OQS/read</A>.
You can subscribe by sending email to <a
href="mailto:OQS-subscribe@topica.com">OQS-subscribe@topica.com</a>.</p>

<p>Please have a look at <A href="http://nipl.net/cgi-bin/wiki/word/">our
wiki</A>.&nbsp; A wiki is a collection of web-pages that anyone can edit.
A wiki is a great way to develop ideas and understanding together.</p>



